                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115/264: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-14T11:00:00+09:00"
                            >May 14, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 14—1:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>308. Department’s 168, May 13, 6 p.m.<note n="13" xml:id="d419fn13">Not printed;
                        comment was asked upon the last paragraph of Shanghai’s telegram No. 639,
                        May 11, 11 a.m., <ref target="#pg_314">p. 314</ref>
                    (393.115/263).</note>—return of American citizens to interior points in China.
                    We perceive no objection whatever to our making formal representations to the
                    Japanese Government in continuation of those already made (see our 125 [<hi
                        rend="italic">225</hi>] April 4, 1 p.m. and despatch No. 2885, April 12<note
                        n="14" xml:id="d419fn14">Latter not printed.</note>). We have subsequently
                    raised this question, together with that of continued occupation of American
                    properties, with the Foreign Office a number of times, and we were told that a
                    plan for satisfactorily concluding these questions is being actively prepared.
                    Nevertheless I shall make further statement early next week unless instructed to
                    the contrary.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Shanghai for Hankow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
